Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.51,0:00:09.79,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,So this fissure was left by your training.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.53,0:00:16.03,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Like a fairy tale
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.03,0:00:18.45,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sign the story has reached its end
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.45,0:00:21.37,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Like a single passage taken from
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.37,0:00:23.00,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,A journey that was too long
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:25.33,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Of the evil that once cast a shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.33,0:00:27.67,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Across this land
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.67,0:00:30.00,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And the memories of the short journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:32.46,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With the hero who defeated it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.26,0:00:42.22,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,473)\blur0.25\fs25\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\pos(322,230)\c&HFFFCFE&\t(989,4326,\c&HEFC777&)\t(6411,6745,\c&HEAC732&)}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.47,0:00:44.77,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The story ends
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.77,0:00:47.27,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And the hero goes to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.27,0:00:50.11,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving this land with
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.11,0:00:51.78,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Days of peace and quiet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.78,0:00:54.28,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The passage of time heartlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.28,0:00:56.45,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Makes people forget
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.45,0:00:59.24,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the tracks left behind by his life
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.24,0:01:01.04,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Begin to rust
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.04,0:01:02.87,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Just the same
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.87,0:01:05.16,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your words and wishes and courage
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.16,0:01:08.50,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Are still inside of me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.50,0:01:10.38,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And they live on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.17,0:01:12.92,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We chose the same path
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.92,0:01:15.05,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,That's all it was supposed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.05,0:01:16.59,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it that at some point
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.59,0:01:20.85,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to understand the reason for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.85,0:01:22.22,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The tears that fall down my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.22,0:01:23.31,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.31,0:01:25.68,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,If I retrace the journey we walked together
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.68,0:01:29.23,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you're not there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.23,0:01:30.90,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'll be able to find it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.99,0:01:46.00,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(397,269.5)}Episode 6: The Hero of the Village
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.82,0:01:56.39,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You don't intend to fight \Nthe dragon, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.08,0:01:59.57,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,So why do you continue training?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.03,0:02:03.14,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,When I arrived here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.14,0:02:07.54,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,all the villagers wore grim expressions \Nand lived in fear of the dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.47,0:02:13.17,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Now those same people are smiling happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:17.27,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,They say this village is safe \Nbecause I'm around,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.17,0:02:20.29,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,even though I haven't done anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.26,0:02:25.65,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,The dragon simply hasn't attacked this \Nvillage because it doesn't feel like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.23,0:02:35.80,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,If the dragon attacks the village, \Nwill you fight it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.13,0:02:37.76,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.16,0:02:43.68,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,But to the people of this village, \NI'm a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.74,0:02:47.12,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Stark, the hero of this village.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.79,0:02:49.86,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I have to defend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.25,0:02:56.69,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That said, maybe I'd actually run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.21,0:03:06.78,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I got this scar on my forehead during a \Nfight with my master, not against monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.36,0:03:14.21,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That was the first time he ever hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.26,0:03:18.31,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been disappointed in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.60,0:03:24.44,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, he never praised me. Not once.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.40,0:03:33.49,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.01,0:03:38.80,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you'll run.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.30,0:03:43.06,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You think you know me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.06,0:03:47.96,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the first thing about you, but \NI recalled my own terrifying experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.96,0:03:49.58,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,A terrifying experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.20,0:03:53.67,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,My first battle against a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:59.63,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd trained plenty until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.03,0:04:02.81,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But my fear made me weak in the knees,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:05.48,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,and I ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.30,0:04:09.34,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The monster wouldn't stop chasing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.79,0:04:12.47,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason, Ms. Frieren \Nwouldn't help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.47,0:04:15.55,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,My master was like that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.55,0:04:17.40,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,When it finally cornered me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.10,0:04:19.73,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,and I steeled my resolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.72,0:04:22.07,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,my body moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.77,0:04:29.98,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,All I needed was resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.67,0:04:34.33,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,All the training you've done \Nwon't let you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.40,0:04:44.14,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Though you're a hopeless coward, I believe \Nyour resolve to protect the village is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.71,0:04:55.15,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Resolve, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.23,0:05:03.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.26,0:05:06.49,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.47,0:05:08.95,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.09,0:05:13.35,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,but I think it'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.38,0:05:24.66,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,He's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.66,0:05:25.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.28,0:05:28.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a shame. I had high hopes for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.54,0:05:29.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.77,0:05:32.55,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern, we're going to play tag \Nwith the dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.55,0:05:33.09,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.77,0:05:37.87,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.23,0:05:42.57,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You need me to keep it busy \Nfor thirty seconds, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:45.49,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.28,0:05:48.61,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Will you promise me one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.61,0:05:52.97,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,If I die during the battle, \NI want you to finish off the dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.71,0:05:56.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.82,0:06:00.83,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But why are you willing to go \Nthat far for the villagers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.59,0:06:04.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.63,0:06:07.70,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I just thought it was a strange question.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.52,0:06:11.22,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I've lived in this village for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.92,0:06:15.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's not very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.07,0:06:16.10,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Like heck it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.18,0:06:23.20,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.70,0:06:25.53,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Your hands are trembling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.53,0:06:27.78,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.59,0:06:31.48,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.06,0:06:33.86,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're just like Eisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.49,0:06:35.87,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,My master?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.05,0:06:39.21,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Now this is a powerful foe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.91,0:06:43.36,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Eisen, your hands are shaking. \NAre you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.37,0:06:45.38,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.87,0:06:47.83,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You'd admit it, just like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.57,0:06:51.65,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Being afraid isn't a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.53,0:06:57.49,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fear that brought me this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.66,0:07:02.85,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You even tremble the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.48,0:07:09.59,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.10,0:07:18.31,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,My master was afraid, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.34,0:07:23.17,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,All I need is resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.11,0:07:28.94,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He's entered the dragon's range.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.10,0:07:31.88,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not attacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.95,0:07:34.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's being cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.75,0:07:37.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.53,0:07:48.39,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder it stopped attacking the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.22,0:07:51.24,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The dragon is a smart creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.85,0:07:55.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not stupid enough to pick a fight \Nagainst a powerful opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.62,0:08:00.16,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Eisen didn't hit Stark for being weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.92,0:08:05.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,or because he was disappointed in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.78,0:08:13.54,FlashbackItalics,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,We parted in anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.29,0:08:15.48,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You hit him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.52,0:08:22.27,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,My body moved on reflex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.87,0:08:25.46,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for what I did to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.26,0:08:28.64,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I was afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:33.29,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I was afraid of him, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.68,0:08:37.15,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.98,0:08:43.62,FlashbackItalics,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,My student will become \Nan incredible warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.18,0:09:19.45,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.13,0:09:25.60,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why aren't you shooting at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.60,0:09:27.59,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I did exactly what you told me to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.97,0:09:29.76,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You expect me to fight it myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.76,0:09:31.83,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious, you old hag!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.15,0:09:33.90,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're just like my master after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.12,0:09:34.64,DefaultOverlap,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.37,0:09:36.23,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.42,0:09:39.00,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,An old hag, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.97,0:09:41.89,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared of what she'll do later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.35,0:09:48.87,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I... killed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.25,0:09:54.55,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I defeated the dragon by myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.39,0:09:57.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.72,0:10:00.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You did well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.42,0:10:03.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You exceeded my expectations. Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.21,0:10:09.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this mountain of treasure. Yippee!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.09,0:10:11.29,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We can't take it all with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.45,0:10:18.22,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,No more than three items.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.21,0:10:24.30,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.67,0:10:26.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're interested in this stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.92,0:10:28.44,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This stuff is a mountain of treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.16,0:10:35.15,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,My master said that you made the \Nheroes' adventure ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.57,0:10:36.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.92,0:10:41.23,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,He said it was a ridiculous and fun journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.36,0:10:48.86,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you actually made shaved ice!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.59,0:10:51.79,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I told you it was worth searching for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.79,0:10:55.03,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but it's \Nfluffy instead of icy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.03,0:10:56.05,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.05,0:11:00.02,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,This is ridiculous. Should we \Nbe wasting time on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.02,0:11:04.42,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Why not? Our journey's only just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.11,0:11:08.70,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,The Hero of the South, said to be \Nhumanity's strongest fighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.70,0:11:11.41,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,was defeated by the Demon King's \NSeven Sages of Destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.53,0:11:17.27,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know if we'll make it back alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.07,0:11:21.65,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Eisen, would you prefer a \Ndifficult and painful journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.91,0:11:32.92,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather enjoy a ridiculous and fun \Njourney I can laugh about when it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:39.54,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Look! It melts as soon as you touch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.54,0:11:41.29,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch it. We're going to eat that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.29,0:11:42.31,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.31,0:11:45.20,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Frieren, what about syrup?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.20,0:11:47.38,Flashback,FREIREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a spell to produce syrup.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.38,0:11:48.23,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.23,0:11:50.25,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Truly ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.03,0:12:07.71,Default,FREIREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Can you see through them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.71,0:12:12.07,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but it's not a very interesting spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.07,0:12:15.03,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry my body's not more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.84,0:12:18.86,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.93,0:12:20.69,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,So small.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.69,0:12:22.45,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not small!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.91,0:12:26.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So, Stark, what will you do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.71,0:12:29.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You can go back to Eisen, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.20,0:12:32.97,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,My master told you to take me \Nwith you, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.67,0:12:34.67,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.72,0:12:39.71,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like going on a \Nridiculous journey, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.57,0:12:49.99,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(903,1)\blur0.2\pos(588.5,15.5)}28 years after the death of Himmel the Hero, in the fortress city of Waal,\Nlocated in Riegel Canyon in the central lands
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:54.51,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters are active in the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.99,0:12:58.59,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,No one's allowed to pass through \Nthe checkpoint currently.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.18,0:13:02.83,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,When will the checkpoint open again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.06,0:13:04.41,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.41,0:13:07.36,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, we've let none \Nthrough since I was posted here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.36,0:13:11.01,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,monsters and people alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:13.59,Default,GUARD,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.35,0:13:17.00,Default,GUARD,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, the castellan would like to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.00,0:13:18.20,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:21.25,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,Listen here, adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.68,0:13:25.31,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cause any trouble in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.32,0:13:32.84,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't a very warm welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.16,0:13:36.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. He's a good guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.88,0:13:38.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Harsh on outsiders,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.06,0:13:42.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,as town guards should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.53,0:13:50.10,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, this city seems safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.10,0:13:52.31,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll wait here for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.43,0:13:56.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a good opportunity \Nto take our time studying magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.70,0:14:00.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Once we drop our things off at the inn, \NI'm going to the magic shops.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.59,0:14:07.83,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What? The checkpoint's closed. \NIt's not like we have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.60,0:14:10.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Go on. You're free to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.65,0:14:12.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to get us a room at the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.08,0:14:16.91,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna get something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.65,0:14:20.41,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Right. I'll go by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.67,0:14:22.90,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.76,0:14:30.96,Default,VILLAGER A,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the sea routes have \Nbeen shut down recently, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.59,0:14:35.03,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,The northern lands' army \Nplans to defeat them,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.03,0:14:38.47,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,but it'll be at least two years \Nuntil the checkpoint opens.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.38,0:14:41.33,Default,VILLAGER B,0000,0000,0000,,Business is at a standstill.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.39,0:14:46.36,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't had this in forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.88,0:14:48.74,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,The jumbo-berry special.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.40,0:14:53.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I was just a kid when I came here before, \Nso I could hardly finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.08,0:14:55.13,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I had to split it with my master.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:14:59.32,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember it being \Nthis small, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.66,0:15:03.96,Default,BARKEEP,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that way because \Nyou're all grown up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.92,0:15:08.98,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I've gotten bigger, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.85,0:15:12.79,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Everything seemed so big when I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.40,0:15:16.58,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Even my master's back that \Nonce looked so broad
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.58,0:15:18.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,started looking small at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.20,0:15:22.95,Default,BARKEEP,0000,0000,0000,,Eisen's getting up there in age.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.95,0:15:25.39,Default,BARKEEP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're being a dutiful student.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.31,0:15:29.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'm doing right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.13,0:15:32.38,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Really, though, was it always {\i1}this{\i0} small?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.38,0:15:35.78,Default,MASTER,0000,0000,0000,,The passage of time is cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.05,0:15:42.75,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What? Got a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.75,0:15:44.53,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I bought it with my own money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.23,0:15:47.64,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Could I get a glass of milk?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.64,0:15:48.82,Default,BARKEEP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.54,0:15:54.04,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why are you mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.09,0:15:56.30,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.30,0:15:58.52,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. You can have half.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.52,0:16:00.18,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I was going to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.95,0:16:05.85,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What if I told you we might have to \Nwait more than two years in this city?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.85,0:16:07.33,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What? No, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.33,0:16:09.83,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Right? I don't want to, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.83,0:16:11.00,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.00,0:16:12.20,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What's her deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.51,0:16:16.77,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm relieved. You're normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.77,0:16:19.70,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did I do something to offend you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.48,0:16:24.35,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,A way through the checkpoint?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.75,0:16:27.53,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I'll help you look for one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.53,0:16:29.34,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.89,0:16:33.35,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be possible to fly over it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.14,0:16:36.53,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The border with the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.53,0:16:39.63,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,is protected by a powerful barrier that \Nextends to maximum flying altitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.63,0:16:41.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be crossed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.59,0:16:45.77,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That makes sense. Otherwise flying \Nmonsters would get right through.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.89,0:16:50.34,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Then we have no choice. \NWe'll hit up the merchants' guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.34,0:16:52.48,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,They might at least be trading.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.42,0:17:06.62,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Trade has been shut down completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.17,0:17:09.91,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,If guarded caravans aren't allowed through,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.91,0:17:12.73,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,then the northern lands \Nmust be quite dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.85,0:17:16.74,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to wait until \Nthe situation settles down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.87,0:17:22.37,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,No, let's hit up the black market \Nand thieves' guild first.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.12,0:17:25.67,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a bit dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.67,0:17:30.98,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be fine. People think I look pretty \Nstrong, and I'm a decent bluffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.15,0:17:33.89,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,And you've got the face of a scoundrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.89,0:17:34.84,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.25,0:17:54.72,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.54,0:17:59.99,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't be surprised. They're \Nbasically fighting a defensive battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.99,0:18:02.30,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing we can do \Nif the gates won't open.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.60,0:18:06.86,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we've got nothing to lose. \NLet's visit the guard station next.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.70,0:18:10.83,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.83,0:18:15.51,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking you're being \Nespecially cooperative.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.51,0:18:17.91,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This was your idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.91,0:18:20.07,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you didn't want to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.49,0:18:23.08,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You seem more desperate than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.63,0:18:28.94,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't have a lot of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.55,0:18:31.00,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.10,0:18:35.95,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,The view from here is nice, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.95,0:18:37.83,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You can see the north side clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.68,0:18:42.22,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,When I was little, \Nmy master brought me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.36,0:18:50.03,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,We departed for the \Nnorthern lands from this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.49,0:18:52.62,Flashback,YOUNG STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What was your journey like, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.33,0:18:57.97,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna know? Back then, we...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.97,0:19:01.11,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Normally he hardly spoke about himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.74,0:19:04.82,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,but he happily told me about \Nthe heroes' adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.00,0:19:08.49,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Across his long life,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.49,0:19:13.01,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,nothing was more important to him \Nthan that ten-year adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.28,0:19:16.74,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure the same is true for Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.28,0:19:19.55,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.91,0:19:24.43,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,But he's too old to travel now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.62,0:19:29.18,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,And he told you to take me with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.35,0:19:37.81,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,So I need to experience lots of \Nridiculous and fun adventures in his place
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.81,0:19:40.94,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,and bring back stories to tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.23,0:19:45.14,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's all I can do to repay my debt to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.55,0:19:50.28,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,If I take too long, my master will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.51,0:19:57.41,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Then we can't allow ourselves \Nto be stopped here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.93,0:20:02.06,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he's still got plenty \Nof years left, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:19.69,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.69,0:20:21.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.17,0:20:23.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm being pursued.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.90,0:20:34.45,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What did you even do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.45,0:20:35.81,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.81,0:20:38.62,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I was just visiting various \Nmagic shops, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.59,0:20:45.87,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Ms. Frieren!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.87,0:20:47.29,Default,GUARD CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.30,0:20:52.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. I don't like where this is going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.77,0:20:57.64,Default,CASTELLAN,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the guard captain was rude to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.13,0:21:01.90,Default,CASTELLAN,0000,0000,0000,,As the castellan of this city, \NI offer my apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.74,0:21:07.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't bother me. He was \Njust doing his job as a guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.40,0:21:10.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually not in any kind of hurry. \NI'm taking my time—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.60,0:21:13.97,Default,CASTELLAN,0000,0000,0000,,You plan to travel north again, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.11,0:21:18.93,Default,CASTELLAN,0000,0000,0000,,I hear the northern lands are currently \Nengaged in an endless conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.93,0:21:21.03,Default,CASTELLAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the remnants of the Demon King's forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.42,0:21:24.18,Default,CASTELLAN,0000,0000,0000,,You must be concerned about \Nthe present situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.18,0:21:27.93,Default,CASTELLAN,0000,0000,0000,,Truly, you have the kindness of a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.46,0:21:32.02,Default,CASTELLAN,0000,0000,0000,,The people of the northern lands \Nwill be delighted as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.02,0:21:35.44,Default,CASTELLAN,0000,0000,0000,,Please feel free to pass \Nthrough the checkpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.62,0:21:51.20,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we're getting\N through this easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.20,0:21:55.28,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't we have told them \Nwho you were from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.04,0:21:58.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think there was any point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.23,0:22:01.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to take my time, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.64,0:22:05.30,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't really like this kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.02,0:22:08.49,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's an unsettling sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.31,0:22:12.10,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad I got to see it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.06,0:22:23.60,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This must be how my master \Ndeparted for the north, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.40,0:22:37.50,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.95,0:22:43.34,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, darn. I wanted to do \Nmore magical research.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.34,0:22:44.66,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're still saying that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.66,0:22:48.34,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We went through a lot of trouble \Nafter that, you know. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.34,0:22:49.15,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.96,0:22:52.50,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And you alright
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.03,0:22:55.02,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hear me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.81,0:23:01.92,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Trailing along deserted train tracks
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.92,0:23:04.25,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Crying excessively
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.81,0:23:07.42,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Wanting you to smile
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.42,0:23:13.46,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I hold on to memories I'd like to keep fresh
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.46,0:23:17.15,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.15,0:23:19.94,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With words more precious than a goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.94,0:23:25.61,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Unremarkable yet special
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.61,0:23:29.13,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.13,0:23:32.18,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.18,0:23:36.94,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.94,0:23:43.04,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if I were to be born again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.04,0:23:48.86,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I would surely choose this place once more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.86,0:23:54.87,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.87,0:24:00.63,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never let you go, I'd choose the present
